  <td valign=3Dtop style=3D'padding:0cm 5.75pt 0cm 5.75pt'>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal>The Lemeresh are almost ethereal in appearance. They=
 are
  large water based life forms. <br>
  <br>
  The Lemeresh live in the deepest oceans of a planet, under the water they
  build leviathan like ships with extremely powerful weaponry. <br>
  <br>
  Little is known about the Lemeresh outside of their appearance and observ=
ing
  their under water ships. They are a race of very few words and do not sha=
re
  any information about themselves with others. <br>
  <br>
  Other races fear that if the Lemeresh are able to somehow convert the aqu=
atic
  based technology in to the vastness of space that they will be unequalled=
 in
  power.</p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'margin-bottom:8.0pt'>The Lemeresh preferred=
 weapon
  is the Phaser and they focus on Power and Shields with Energy Research.</=
p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal><i style=3D'mso-bidi-font-style:normal'>This race is=
 very
  insular and secretive. They are not war like but can be a massive road bl=
ock
  in the Galaxy because of their huge power early on. Conquering them as a
  player will not be easy at all once the Lemeresh are established. They are
  not meant to be played because they will have a big advantage to the play=
er,
  they are designed to be a significant faction that brings it's own
  challenges. I left them playable simply in case someone wanted to try it
  although I don't recommend it.<o:p></o:p></i></p>
